{
  "stem": "22972.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother had lived in Cleveland for a year, instead of going to finishing school, and my father had lived in London for five years.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they both spoke English.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he said, of course I'm related to Michael Friedsam.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's only-- the Friedsam family is only one single family all over the world.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he said, well, in that case, I welcome you to your new home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he went bang, bang, bang, bang and we were the first people-- I mean, we weren't first class on the boat, but we were the first, literally, the first people off that boat.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my father, who had thought about changing the name Friedsam and Americanizing the name, said, I'm not going to change my name if the name is that famous in New York.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This little man, the immigration officer, was the first and last person that we ever came across who knew the name Friedsam, except that Michael Friedsam has a big statue.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was a major philanthropist in New York City.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He gave his art collection to the Metropolitan Museum of Art, and he was a very important person, but nobody has ever heard of him today.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "This was around the turn of the century or shortly thereafter, and the name Friedsam doesn't mean-- Yes, there is a Friedsam Carousel in Central Park, but very few people-- most people just call it the Carousel in Central Park.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They don't call it the Friedsam Carousel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There is a sign, however, and I do have a picture of it, but I don't have it here.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There are a couple of things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of them I started to mention, and that, again, my father-- you could not take money out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
